WEBVTT

00:02.507 --> 00:04.820
[ Wind Whistling ]

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:22.181 --> 00:24.955
[ Man ]
Viewer beware.

00:24.955 --> 00:27.995
You're in for a scare.

00:30.121 --> 00:32.393
Goosebumps.

00:32.961 --> 00:35.300
[ Wolf Howling ]

02:05.310 --> 02:09.180
Hey, kid,
aren't you forgetting something?

02:10.225 --> 02:12.973
You said you were gonna
be here for a month.

02:12.973 --> 02:16.634
- Probably gonna need these.
- Thanks.

02:16.634 --> 02:19.696
Pretty creepy around these parts,
huh?

02:19.696 --> 02:23.829
Yeah, well, my aunt and uncle
should be here any minute, so...

02:25.667 --> 02:28.319
I heard a story once
about a headless ghost

02:28.319 --> 02:30.645
supposed to be out in those woods...

02:30.645 --> 02:33.690
and every night,
when they moon is full,

02:33.690 --> 02:37.728
he haunts the forest,
seeking revenge.

02:37.728 --> 02:41.987
"Give me back my head...
give me back my head!"

02:41.987 --> 02:46.437
Don't you have some kind
of schedule to keep?

02:47.538 --> 02:49.504
You'll be all right, kid.

02:49.504 --> 02:52.857
Sun should be coming up...
eventually.

02:52.857 --> 02:56.516
Have a nice night!
[ Laughing ]

03:10.716 --> 03:12.335
[ Sighs ]

03:22.898 --> 03:26.222
[ Wolves Howl ]

03:31.553 --> 03:34.670
[ Reading ] "Attention
all photographers. Enter today."

03:45.404 --> 03:47.615
Hmm.

04:19.190 --> 04:23.752
[ Thinking ] Wolf Creek.
Wonder where they got that name?

04:27.782 --> 04:31.431
[ Wolf Howls ]

04:32.212 --> 04:34.505
[ Growling ]

04:39.534 --> 04:42.866
[ Wolves Howling ]

04:46.865 --> 04:50.536
[ Rooster Crowing ]

05:27.470 --> 05:29.105
[ Gasps ]

05:31.044 --> 05:34.430
Careful, city boy.
That might be a killer bunny.

05:34.430 --> 05:37.344
- Uncle Colin.
- How you doin', chief? Ooh!

05:37.344 --> 05:39.667
- Oh, sorry.
- That's OK. That's OK.

05:39.667 --> 05:43.290
Sorry I'm late.
Jeep's been acting up lately.

05:44.633 --> 05:46.863
So, your birthday
present still working?

05:46.863 --> 05:48.984
Yeah. I was wondering
if you and Aunt Marta

05:48.984 --> 05:50.826
could take me on one of your shoots.

05:50.826 --> 05:52.975
You know,
give me a couple of tips.

05:52.975 --> 05:54.817
Not much to it.
Just point and snap.

05:54.817 --> 05:58.015
Subject is what's important.
You gotta find that one thing

05:58.015 --> 06:01.439
that nobody's ever seen before
and show it to them.

06:01.439 --> 06:03.327
Hopefully, in focus.

06:03.327 --> 06:05.034
Have you heard from
Mom and Dad yet?

06:05.034 --> 06:06.749
Yup.
They called from London this morning.

06:06.749 --> 06:09.577
They arrived safe and sound.

06:09.577 --> 06:12.214
Let's hope that we can do the same.

06:12.214 --> 06:16.227
- What do you mean?
- Fasten your seat belt.

06:16.227 --> 06:19.547
We're gonna take a shortcut.

06:53.861 --> 06:56.195
[ Honks Horn ]

06:56.195 --> 06:58.503
[ Uncle ]
Here you are, champ.

06:58.503 --> 07:01.972
Man, that was better
than a roller coaster.

07:01.972 --> 07:04.934
You got in that Jeep with him?

07:04.934 --> 07:07.507
You're lucky to be alive.
I resent that.

07:07.507 --> 07:11.364
- Hi, Aunt Marta.
- Look how big you're getting.

07:11.364 --> 07:13.352
What are you, 8 feet tall now?

07:13.352 --> 07:16.319
Alex brought his camera with him.
He's hoping we'll give him a lesson.

07:16.319 --> 07:17.986
I'm entering a photography contest.

07:17.986 --> 07:20.092
First prize is 1,000 bucks,
and your picture goes

07:20.092 --> 07:21.528
on the cover of Chiller magazine.

07:21.528 --> 07:24.032
Chiller magazine--
and what kind of pictures

07:24.032 --> 07:26.398
are they looking for,
as if I have to ask.

07:26.398 --> 07:27.680
Something scary.

07:27.680 --> 07:29.031
It's supposed to make
the reader shudder.

07:29.031 --> 07:32.432
- You'll be out of luck around here.
- I'm afraid he's right.

07:32.432 --> 07:34.777
There's nothing particularly
scary about Wolf Creek.

07:34.777 --> 07:37.429
- What about that place?
- That's the Marlings' house.

07:37.429 --> 07:40.326
You wanna stay away from
the couple. They're crazy.

07:40.326 --> 07:43.087
Honey, don't say crazy.
They're just eccentric.

07:43.087 --> 07:45.962
They're nuts.

07:45.962 --> 07:48.987
It's probably a good idea
just to leave them alone.

07:48.987 --> 07:51.477
[ Sniffs ]
Oh, my gosh!

07:51.477 --> 07:54.195
- What?
- I'm making french toast for breakfast,

07:54.195 --> 07:58.258
only by the smell of things,
I think it just became charcoal.

08:00.754 --> 08:05.398
I bet I can get some great shots in there.

08:18.664 --> 08:20.743
[ Clattering ]

08:33.626 --> 08:35.671
Alex, rule number 2:

08:35.671 --> 08:38.589
if you wanna be
a good photographer,

08:38.589 --> 08:42.345
- don't leave your camera in the Jeep.
- Right.

08:42.345 --> 08:46.074
- What's rule number one?
- Take some pictures.

08:48.116 --> 08:49.567
Thanks.

09:45.603 --> 09:47.908
[ Rattling ]

10:06.024 --> 10:09.930
Something to make people
shudder, hmm...

10:12.827 --> 10:15.060
That's kinda creepy.

10:22.683 --> 10:26.116
Don't worry. I don't bite.

10:26.116 --> 10:29.067
I just didn't expect
to see anybody here.

10:29.067 --> 10:32.364
I come here all the time,
I love this forest.

10:32.364 --> 10:35.101
They're gonna cut it all down
and put up a mall,

10:35.101 --> 10:38.394
like we need any more video arcades,
I'm Hannah Stoneman.

10:38.394 --> 10:40.908
- Alex Blackwell.
- Yeah, I know.

10:40.908 --> 10:43.181
Colin and Marta's nephew, right?
The city boy.

10:43.181 --> 10:46.491
- Yeah, I guess.
- Come on, let me give you a tour.

10:46.491 --> 10:50.051
- Cool.
- That's a tree... and that's a rock...

10:50.051 --> 10:52.497
and that flying thing there's a bird.

10:52.497 --> 10:57.286
Really? Wow, thanks!
What a great guide.

10:58.411 --> 11:00.888
So, what's it like living in the city?

11:00.888 --> 11:03.587
OK, I guess.
There's lots to do.

11:03.587 --> 11:06.582
Sometime it gets
kinda crowded and noisy,

11:06.582 --> 11:10.390
- but you get used to it.
- I'd like to go there sometime.

11:10.390 --> 11:13.074
What do you mean?
Never been to a city?

11:13.074 --> 11:15.542
I've never been out of Wolf Creek.

11:15.542 --> 11:20.408
Wow, so, what do you and
your friends do for fun around here?

11:20.408 --> 11:25.740
Friends? Well, um, I mostly
just hang out with myself.

11:25.740 --> 11:29.098
- I like to be alone.
- Why?

11:30.781 --> 11:33.387
The sun's going down.
We better get home.

11:33.387 --> 11:35.302
Hannah, wait up.
What's the rush?

11:35.303 --> 11:38.254
The woods aren't really safe
after dark.

11:38.254 --> 11:40.870
Why? Is that when the monsters
come out or something?

11:40.870 --> 11:44.911
- That's not funny, Alex.
- Gee. It was just a joke.

11:47.422 --> 11:51.704
Hannah, wait a second.
I want to get a picture of this.

11:54.124 --> 11:56.357
Cool. Got it.

11:57.728 --> 11:59.957
Hannah?

12:01.570 --> 12:05.003
Hannah? Great.

12:05.003 --> 12:06.978
Thanks a lot.

12:09.881 --> 12:13.858
"Come to the country a while, Alex."

12:13.858 --> 12:18.886
"Get back to nature, Alex."
Yeah, right.

12:19.897 --> 12:23.265
[ Sighs ]
Um, then we came that way, and...

12:23.265 --> 12:25.737
no, it was that way.

12:25.737 --> 12:28.010
- Or was it that way?
- [ Growl ]

12:28.010 --> 12:30.349
[ Gasp ] Hannah?

12:30.349 --> 12:32.734
Hannah, is that you?

12:34.874 --> 12:38.038
Who is it?
Who's out there?

12:42.631 --> 12:45.002
Probably just another rabbit.

12:48.592 --> 12:50.793
[ Screams ]

12:51.313 --> 12:53.476
That's no rabbit!

13:04.804 --> 13:06.735
Help!

13:06.735 --> 13:08.228
Help!

13:08.228 --> 13:10.808
It's gonna get me!

13:10.808 --> 13:13.805
Let me in! Help!

13:14.939 --> 13:17.220
Let me in! Help me!

13:17.220 --> 13:19.500
Alex! Alex, calm down.

13:19.500 --> 13:22.503
There was something out there.
It was chasing me.

13:22.503 --> 13:24.191
What were you doing
out in the woods?

13:24.191 --> 13:27.088
- Just taking some pictures--
- You shouldn't be out there after dark.

13:27.088 --> 13:31.228
It's not safe. And what did
we say about the Marlings?

13:31.228 --> 13:34.630
- But something was after me--
- What did we say about the Marlings?!

13:34.630 --> 13:39.865
- Not to bother them, I know, but--
- Then it had better not happen again.

13:40.912 --> 13:42.876
Come on.

13:45.984 --> 13:48.773
- Where's Uncle Colin?
- Shooting, we've been waiting

13:48.773 --> 13:50.458
for you to come home
for over an hour,

13:50.458 --> 13:52.381
but he finally had to go on ahead.

13:52.381 --> 13:55.965
- Can I come, too?
- No!

13:58.949 --> 14:01.662
Look, Alex, we're working
on a special project tonight,

14:01.662 --> 14:04.279
and the fewer bodies we have
around, the better.

14:04.296 --> 14:05.672
What's the project?

14:05.672 --> 14:08.166
Alex, I don't have time
for all these questions.

14:08.166 --> 14:11.596
I want you to get in that house
and stay there.

14:11.596 --> 14:13.522
Is that understood?

14:20.428 --> 14:24.050
- Is it?
- Yes.

14:24.050 --> 14:25.624
Good.

14:28.434 --> 14:31.537
And stay out of the woods.

14:34.548 --> 14:37.515
[ Tires Squeal ]

14:41.105 --> 14:44.563
Legend. Now, who can tell us
what this word means?

14:44.563 --> 14:46.903
Anyone?
What about you, Alex?

14:46.903 --> 14:49.015
Well, it's like a fairy tale.

14:49.015 --> 14:53.254
It's a... lie that people believe
in because they don't know

14:53.254 --> 14:56.422
- that real reason for things.
- That's very good, Alex.

14:56.422 --> 15:00.698
- "That's very good, Alex."
- Do you have something to add, Sean?

15:00.698 --> 15:04.597
Yeah. Just 'cause something's
a legend doesn't mean it's not true.

15:04.597 --> 15:07.158
Yeah... not true.

15:07.158 --> 15:09.419
Do you care ot give us
an example, Sean?

15:09.419 --> 15:11.791
Sure.
How about werewolves?

15:11.791 --> 15:15.254
- Werewolves.
- You think that's funny?

15:15.254 --> 15:18.327
Yeah. I mean, no one
believes in werewolves.

15:19.588 --> 15:21.262
Right?

15:24.578 --> 15:26.735
Right?

15:29.685 --> 15:33.715
- Do you believe the legend, Sean?
- Some of it.

15:33.715 --> 15:36.239
Like, if someone
is bit by a werewolf,

15:36.239 --> 15:39.839
they'll be cursed,
and when the moon is full,

15:39.839 --> 15:45.286
- they'll turn into a werewolf, too.
- Yeah... werewolf.

15:45.286 --> 15:47.953
And you can only kill 'em
with a silver bullet, right?

15:47.953 --> 15:50.823
That's the part of
the legend that's not true.

15:50.823 --> 15:53.432
What really happens
is when the sun rises

15:53.432 --> 15:56.837
a werewolf sheds its skin,
and if someone finds the skin

15:56.837 --> 15:58.701
and destroys it before
the next full moon

15:58.701 --> 16:00.858
is at its highest point,
the curse is over,

16:00.858 --> 16:04.122
and the werewolf
inside the person dies.

16:04.122 --> 16:07.109
Yeah... dies.

16:07.109 --> 16:09.406
Where did you hear that legend,
Sean?

16:09.406 --> 16:12.617
Around. You live in
Wolf Creek long enough,

16:12.617 --> 16:17.145
- you hear lots of things.
- Or you go crazy.

16:22.571 --> 16:24.131
[ Bell Rings ]

16:24.131 --> 16:28.827
Oh, for tomorrow,
remember to read chapter 13.

16:42.676 --> 16:45.273
You think I'm funny, huh?

16:45.273 --> 16:47.550
Is that why you were laughing at me?

16:47.550 --> 16:49.122
Yeah... laughing at him?

16:49.122 --> 16:51.305
Look, I didn't mean anything, OK?

16:51.305 --> 16:56.970
It's just... you two look like,
uh, pretty intelligent guys,

16:56.970 --> 17:00.058
and I'm surprised you believe in
something as stupid as werewolves.

17:00.058 --> 17:03.116
It's not stupid, man.
It's true, and we can prove it,

17:03.116 --> 17:06.826
- if you're brave enough.
- Yeah... brave enough.

17:06.826 --> 17:09.605
- How?
- Out behind the Marlings' house,

17:09.605 --> 17:12.055
there's a fallen tree that
goes right across Wolf Creek.

17:12.055 --> 17:13.523
Yeah. What about it?

17:13.523 --> 17:15.723
That's where the werewolves
go to drink water out of the river.

17:15.723 --> 17:17.388
Meet us there, midnight tonight.

17:17.388 --> 17:20.011
You'll get your proof,
unless you're chicken.

17:20.011 --> 17:24.752
Yeah... chicken.
Cluck, cluck, cluck--

17:24.752 --> 17:28.160
- Zip it, Arjun.
- Can I bring my camera?

17:28.160 --> 17:32.836
- It's a free country.
- OK, I'm there. Midnight.

17:34.067 --> 17:36.157
See you tonight.

17:41.195 --> 17:45.065
Maybe I'll get a picture.
Yeah.

18:11.541 --> 18:14.027
[ Wing Flapping ]

18:23.954 --> 18:27.281
[ Gasps ] Why does everyone
around here do that?

18:27.281 --> 18:29.589
I heard what Sean
and Arjun said to you.

18:29.589 --> 18:32.020
About tonight.
You're not gonna go, are you?

18:32.020 --> 18:33.832
Are you kidding?
And let those guys

18:33.832 --> 18:35.623
think I'm chicken or something?
No way.

18:35.623 --> 18:37.889
But, Alex, it's in the woods,
after dark.

18:37.889 --> 18:40.849
- I told you before, it's not safe.
- Hannah, get a grip.

18:40.849 --> 18:43.223
It's not like I'll be alone there
or anything.

18:43.223 --> 18:45.640
Besides, if something
does come after us.

18:45.640 --> 18:48.415
- It'll go for Sean first.
- He's big. He's a better meal.

18:48.415 --> 18:50.520
This isn't a joke, Alex.
You could get hurt.

18:50.520 --> 18:52.472
Nothing's gonna happen
my aunt and uncle

18:52.472 --> 18:54.780
are going out on
another shoot tonight.

18:54.780 --> 18:57.276
I'll wait until they're gone,
meet up with Beavis and Butt-head,

18:57.276 --> 18:58.758
take a couple pictures,
and be back

18:58.758 --> 19:01.520
before any werewolves
even know I'm there.

19:01.520 --> 19:03.706
Oh, they'll know, ALex,
and they'll find you.

19:03.706 --> 19:06.483
Please, don't tell me
you believe in that stuff, too.

19:06.483 --> 19:08.698
Please don't go.

19:08.698 --> 19:12.322
Hannah... Hannah!

19:12.322 --> 19:15.155
Man!
These people are weird.

19:27.342 --> 19:30.495
[ Alarm Buzzes ]

19:43.018 --> 19:47.574
What?
They locked me in.

19:49.667 --> 19:51.368
Ah.

19:53.238 --> 19:56.252
What is this, alcatraz?

20:27.070 --> 20:31.718
I've been at Wolf Creek too long.
I'm starting to see things, too.

20:34.286 --> 20:36.846
[ Screams ]

20:36.846 --> 20:39.000
[ Snarling ]

20:41.509 --> 20:44.368
Wolf!

